  <div class="column_holder">
    <h1>
      <img alt="JOBS" src="/images/headers/pf_heading/dynamicimage.aspx?text=JOBS" />
    </h1>
    <div class="column_heading">
      <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblTop"><p>GRIN is constantly looking for talented people. All available positions are listed below. Apply via the form or by e-mail.  If you are interested in a position that isn&rsquo;t listed, please send your CV via e-mail to jobs@grin.se.</p></span></div>
    <div class="column_sep">
      <img src="img/jobs/jobs_open_sep.png" alt="Open positions" /></div>
    
    
      <div class="column_content">
        <h1>
          <img alt="Wednesday 11 March 2009" src="/images/headers/pf_small/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Wednesday 11 March 2009" />
        </h1>
        <h2>
          <img alt="Experienced Animator - Barcelona" src="/images/headers/pf_heading/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Experienced Animator - Barcelona" />
        </h2>
        <p>
          <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText"><p>GRIN, developers of hits Ghost Recon Advanced Warfighter 1 &amp; 2 and the upcoming titles Bionic Commando, Terminator Salvation&nbsp;and Wanted, are seeking a full time Experienced Animator to work closely within our animation team in Barcelona to create a wide variety of moves for characters to be used on an upcoming title for the major consoles. The ideal candidate will be self motivated, have a good eye for detail and an ability to bring life to in-game characters. <br />
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities</strong><br />
&bull; Create quality animation in a timely manner<br />
&bull; Work closely with multiple departments to troubleshoot and solve technical animation issues.<br />
&bull; Respond positively to direction and work reviews to meet game vision on animations. <br />
&bull; Assist with information regarding planning production schedules.<br />
&bull; (Learn and) use software and in house tools.<br />
&bull; Providing mentoring to juniors.<br />
<br />
<strong>Requirements</strong><br />
&bull; Strong motion capture editing and key frame animations skills.<br />
&bull; Good knowledge of Motion Builder and Maya. <br />
&bull; Quality awareness for next gen games- Ability to self-crit work as well as actively participating in reviews.<br />
&bull; Strong understanding of fundamental animation principals and their application within a game&rsquo;s technical dependencies. A solid sense of weight and balance essential. <br />
&bull; 2+ years of professional experience as an animator, preferably in games industry. <br />
&bull; Ability to create cinematic content <br />
&bull; Respond well to direction, and excel in a team environment. <br />
&bull; Excellent personal task management skills, prioritizing multiple tasks and meeting deadlines. <br />
&bull; Assistance with motion capture shoots when required desirable. <br />
&bull; Good technical abilities with respect to the implementation of animation into a game engine. <br />
&bull; Understand animation pipeline and how this fits into the broader game production cycle. <br />
&bull; Good level of English is mandatory. <br />
<br />
<strong>Desired Skills and Pluses</strong><br />
&bull; Passionate about games. <br />
&bull; Drawing skills, cinematic knowledge and conceptual art ability as well as Rigging, Modeling and texturing.<br />
<br />
Apply via mail - <a href="mailto:eab@grin.se">eab@grin.se</a></p></span></p>
      </div>
      <div class="column_nav">
        <span class="column_nav_cat">Contact</span>
        <p>
          Please send your application through the online form below, or by regular mail to
          our physical adress. If you prefer to send your application by email click
          <a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#101;&#97;&#98;&#64;&#103;&#114;&#105;&#110;&#46;&#115;&#101;">here</a>.</p>
      </div>
